For your bump today you get a new cookie to try!

Cream Cheese Cookies

1 cup butter, margarine, or shortening
2 pkg. (3 oz. each) cream cheese
1 cup granulated sugar
1 tsp. vanilla
2 egg yolks
2 cups flour
1 tsp. salt
3/4 cup almonds, pecans, or cashews

Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Add nuts, if desired.
Drop by tsp. on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 F. for 10 minutes.

Oquies
No Bake cookies! Go try them. They are my favorite cookie at least.

Ingredients

1 3/4 cups white sugar
1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup butter
4 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder
1/2 cup crunchy peanut butter
3 cups quick-cooking oats
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Directions

In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa. Bring to a boil, and cook for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat, and stir in peanut butter, oats, and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool until hardened.

On july 12, 2012
Ramza

I was just thinking that the best thing in this on-line gaming is the society. Ive been playing DinoRPG since 2009 just for my own pleasure. I liked the limited daily turns system and the level of different possibilities that this game offers. And then, suddenly, things changed.
After 2 years of playing I have decided to join a clan!
OK then which should I choose? Oh, look, this one looks like fun! THE COOKIES!
I applied. Soon enough a message arrived:
- Why do you want to join our clan?
- Because you are strong, you are nice, and you promise that I will have fun!
And so I was accepted. A noob with 3x lvl30 dinoz (and it was just a little more than a year ago!).

Being in a clan has taken this game to a totally different level. All because of Clan Events like COTC and Clan Wars. Ive joined right after the Clan War (which I was totally not aware of at that moment). Ive met masters like PerrBear2 or Lolwhut and Ive learned that there is something called a dojo! I was learning something new every day and it was cool.
And then came my first clan event. COTC! I had no dinoz strong enough to participate, so Ive quickly learned the rules (some terrific guides on clanpages!) and I was helping in coordination and planning. Surprisingly I was awarded with a *star* for my efforts!

In the meantime Ive learned that my account is rubbish and I decided to start anew. Ive frozen all of my dinoz and Ive bought new ones. It took a while, but now my account at least makes sense. I still dont have dinoz capable of fighting at the highest level but Ill get there soon enough!
My second event was a Clan War. My third - another Clan War. I've managed to get another *star* for leading a clan in the first stage of the war! We've placed 3rd!
But I was waiting patiently (which was hard at times) for the COTC to be back. And it finally came!

I have to admit that nothing beats COTC! The level of planning and coordination required to play a good battle is overwhelming at times. You need to have a devoted team to be successful in COTC and The Cookies have made my time during this one the most exciting. We didn't have a specific goal for this event. Of course we wanted 3 Napos, but we also had to be realistic. With AndySQdancer and Nyphanalith being inactive we were losing a lot of strength. We had to make it up with something else...
Our planning and strategy has been put on the shoulders of Hailstone, our quite new recruit, who has proven most skilled in this. He was coordinating the beginning of each battle so that we didnt waste irmas. He was thinking of a best defence line and making sure that each person on board knew where and when to go. Of course he couldnt have done all this without the help of many others who were available on IRC. The discussion about the strategy and next moves was always ongoing and new ideas were popping from everywhere.
The activity in our clan always skyrockets during events and it was not uncommon to see 20+ people on IRC at one moment! This was amazing. Some of them were watching and moving their dinoz on board, but some were just cheering and watching and raising our spirits up.
The best battle Ive had so far in COTC was The Cookies vs LBT. We knew that Hailstone will be away, but the thirst for winning this battle was high enough to make it the reality. It was such an epic view, when I saw a note on our clanforum saying:
Please join the battle with dinoz lvl 35+. They are considered high level now!!!
This alone says everything about the intensity of the battle. Everyone wanted to win this and everyone contributed the way they could. And weve won.

Great, friendly atmosphere, people who are more than game buddies, engagement, good organisation and planning, strong players, and each and every one of them having so much fun! All of this has taken us to the 2nd place in this COTC which is definitely above our real strength. Amazing!

Here are some thought from our clanforum:
Be proud of yourself! Creating a FUN clan that always stayed a fun clan and made it to the final of a major event is incredible!
We can be very proud that we're one of the few clans that didn't recruit after the group stages... and we still made it all the way to the final

So, dear dinoz Master, if you want to try something new, feel the difference between good and great, if you think that you can be a part of this family and can participate in clan events...
And above all, you want to have FUN playing this game, come join us! Our recruitment is open for players who can help us grow and thrive! The requirements are:
- have at least 3 dinoz lvl 45+
- be active!


Im happy to be a part of this clan more and more with every passing day. Im sure you will be too!

Cheers,
Ramza
